None, 'body': "On Visual Studio 2022 Version 17.1.2, Windows 10 Pro 19044.1586

## Repro: 

1. Install Porting Assistant vs2022 Extension ;)
2. Open Visual Studio, Create New .Net Framework Project v4.7.2
- In Porting Assistant menu, add settings, target .Net 6.0 and relevant creds
- Run Full Assessment
- Close solution
- Reopen solution
  - Get Error `Activating language client: Porting Assistant`
  - `Your task failed with the message: The type initializer for 'PortingAssistantVSExtensionClient.Options.UserSettings' threw an exception`
  - 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2111973/160171159-9f519047-ea9e-47ea-a86d-6131624684b6.png)
Also get error trying to access the porting assistant settings
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/2111973/160171342-faab48f1-4c75-4fb0-a646-390d8f0963c6.png)



## Workaround
- In project folder, delete the `.vs` folder
- Everything works again until you close the solution.
